{"parse":{"title":"Ruth DeFries","pageid":19346578,"revid":851717786,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">Ruth DeFries</span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n1957</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma&#160;mater</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Washington_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Washington University\">Washington University</a>;<br /><a href=\"/wiki/Johns_Hopkins_University\" title=\"Johns Hopkins University\">Johns Hopkins University</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Awards</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/MacArthur_Fellowship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MacArthur Fellowship\">MacArthur Fellowship</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<b>Scientific career</b></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Fields</th><td class=\"category\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_geography\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Environmental geography\">Environmental geography</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University</a>;<br /> <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Maryland,_College_Park\" title=\"University of Maryland, College Park\">University of Maryland, College Park</a></td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Ruth DeFries</b> (born 1957) is an <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_geography\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Environmental geography\">environmental geographer</a> who specializes in the use of <a href=\"/wiki/Remote_sensing\" title=\"Remote sensing\">remote sensing</a> to study Earth's habitability under the influence of human activities, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Deforestation\" title=\"Deforestation\">deforestation</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> that influence regulating <a href=\"/wiki/Biophysics\" title=\"Biophysics\">biophysical</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Biogeochemistry\" title=\"Biogeochemistry\">biogeochemical</a> processes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BIO_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BIO-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> She was one of 24 recipients of the 2007 <a href=\"/wiki/MacArthur_Fellowship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"MacArthur Fellowship\">MacArthur Fellowship</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and was elected to the <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_National_Academy_of_Sciences\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"United States National Academy of Sciences\">United States National Academy of Sciences</a> in 2006.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#An_Ecomodernist_Manifesto\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">An Ecomodernist Manifesto</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Works</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Books\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Scientific_Papers\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Scientific Papers</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Awards\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Awards</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Life\">Life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>DeFries received her Ph.D. in 1980 from the Department of Geography and <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_Engineering\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Environmental Engineering\">Environmental Engineering</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Johns_Hopkins_University\" title=\"Johns Hopkins University\">Johns Hopkins University</a> and her B.A. in Earth Science in 1976 from <a href=\"/wiki/Washington_University\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Washington University\">Washington University</a>. In April 2016, <a href=\"/wiki/Columbia_University\" title=\"Columbia University\">Columbia University</a> named her a University Professor, its highest academic rank. She had previously been the Denning Family Professor of <a href=\"/wiki/Sustainable_Development\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sustainable Development\">Sustainable Development</a> in Columbia's Department of <a href=\"/wiki/Ecology\" title=\"Ecology\">Ecology</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Evolution\" title=\"Evolution\">Evolution</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Environmental_Biology\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Environmental Biology\">Environmental Biology</a>. Before moving to Columbia in 2008, she was a professor at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Maryland,_College_Park\" title=\"University of Maryland, College Park\">University of Maryland, College Park</a> with joint appointments in the Department of Geography and the Earth System Science Interdisciplinary Center.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BIO_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BIO-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"An_Ecomodernist_Manifesto\">An Ecomodernist Manifesto</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: An Ecomodernist Manifesto\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In April 2015, DeFries joined with a group of scholars in issuing <i>An Ecomodernist Manifesto</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-EcoModernistManifesto_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-EcoModernistManifesto-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NYT41415_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NYT41415-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> The other authors were: John Asafu-Adjaye, Linus Blomqvist, <a href=\"/wiki/Stewart_Brand\" title=\"Stewart Brand\">Stewart Brand</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Barry_Brook_(scientist)\" title=\"Barry Brook (scientist)\">Barry Brook</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Erle_Ellis\" title=\"Erle Ellis\">Erle Ellis</a>, Christopher Foreman, <a href=\"/wiki/David_Keith_(scientist)\" title=\"David Keith (scientist)\">David Keith</a>, Martin Lewis, <a href=\"/wiki/Mark_Lynas\" title=\"Mark Lynas\">Mark Lynas</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Ted_Nordhaus\" title=\"Ted Nordhaus\">Ted Nordhaus</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Roger_A._Pielke,_Jr.\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Roger A. Pielke, Jr.\">Roger A. Pielke, Jr.</a>, Rachel Pritzker, Joyashree Roy, Mark Sagoff, <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Shellenberger\" title=\"Michael Shellenberger\">Michael Shellenberger</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Stone_(director)\" title=\"Robert Stone (director)\">Robert Stone</a>, and Peter Teague<sup id=\"cite_ref-EcoModernismAuthors_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-EcoModernismAuthors-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Also see <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Sustainable_development\" title=\"Portal:Sustainable development\">Portal:Sustainable development</a>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Works\">Works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books\">Books</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Books\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>The Big Ratchet: How Humanity Thrives in the Face of Natural Crisis (2014) Basic Books<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Scientific_Papers\">Scientific Papers</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Scientific Papers\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>DeFries is the author or co-author of over 100 scientific papers on such topics as: Impacts of Tropical Fires on Air Quality and Greenhouse Gas Emissions; Land Use, Nutrition, and Food Security; Land Use and Conservation in the Tropics; Climate and Tropical Agriculture; Processes of Tropical Deforestation and Degradation; Methods for Remote Sensing of Land Cover; and Reviews and Conceptual Papers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Awards\">Awards</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Awards\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>2007 <a href=\"/wiki/MacArthur_Fellows_Program\" title=\"MacArthur Fellows Program\">MacArthur Fellows Program</a></li>\n<li>2015 Breakthrough Paradigm Award<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ruth_DeFries&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-7451676_ITM\">\"Maryland-Led Research Revises Estimates of Tropical Deforestation\"</a>. Ascribe Higher Education News Service. 2002-10-14<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Maryland-Led+Research+Revises+Estimates+of+Tropical+Deforestation.&amp;rft.date=2002-10-14&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.accessmylibrary.com%2Fcoms2%2Fsummary_0286-7451676_ITM&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2001/06/010605072649.htm\">\"An Improved Method For Monitoring National And Global Deforestation\"</a>. ScienceDaily. 2001-06-05<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=An+Improved+Method+For+Monitoring+National+And+Global+Deforestation&amp;rft.pub=ScienceDaily&amp;rft.date=2001-06-05&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2001%2F06%2F010605072649.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2006/09/060920092900.htm\">\"Growth In Amazon Cropland May Impact Climate And Deforestation Patterns\"</a>. ScienceDaily. 2006-09-22<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Growth+In+Amazon+Cropland+May+Impact+Climate+And+Deforestation+Patterns&amp;rft.pub=ScienceDaily&amp;rft.date=2006-09-22&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedaily.com%2Freleases%2F2006%2F09%2F060920092900.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-BIO-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-BIO_4-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-BIO_4-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.earth.columbia.edu/ac/bios/defries.html\">\"Ruth DeFries biography\"</a>. The Earth Institute, Columbia University<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Ruth+DeFries+biography&amp;rft.pub=The+Earth+Institute%2C+Columbia+University&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.earth.columbia.edu%2Fac%2Fbios%2Fdefries.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.macfound.org/site/c.lkLXJ8MQKrH/b.2913825/apps/nl/content2.asp?content_id={FACCE0E3-8520-4752-9B5D-0F05779C3340}&amp;notoc=1\">\"MacArthur Fellows 2007\"</a>. The John D. and Catherine T. MacArthur Foundation<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=MacArthur+Fellows+2007&amp;rft.pub=The+John+D.+and+Catherine+T.+MacArthur+Foundation&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.macfound.org%2Fsite%2Fc.lkLXJ8MQKrH%2Fb.2913825%2Fapps%2Fnl%2Fcontent2.asp%3Fcontent_id%3D%7BFACCE0E3-8520-4752-9B5D-0F05779C3340%7D%26notoc%3D1&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Roylance, Frank D.; Emery, Chris (2007-09-25). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-32968352_ITM\">\"<span style=\"padding-left:0.2em;\">'</span>Genius' rewarded: Hopkins physician, UM geographer are among 24 awarded $500,000 MacArthur grants for research\"</a>. Baltimore Sun<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=%27Genius%27+rewarded%3A+Hopkins+physician%2C+UM+geographer+are+among+24+awarded+%24500%2C000+MacArthur+grants+for+research.&amp;rft.date=2007-09-25&amp;rft.aulast=Roylance&amp;rft.aufirst=Frank+D.&amp;rft.au=Emery%2C+Chris&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.accessmylibrary.com%2Fcoms2%2Fsummary_0286-32968352_ITM&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.newsdesk.umd.edu/scitech/release.cfm?ArticleID=1277\">\"A Conversation with UM's Ruth DeFries, Newly Elected to the National Academy of Sciences\"</a>. University of Maryland<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-09-16</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=A+Conversation+with+UM%27s+Ruth+DeFries%2C+Newly+Elected+to+the+National+Academy+of+Sciences&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Maryland&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsdesk.umd.edu%2Fscitech%2Frelease.cfm%3FArticleID%3D1277&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-EcoModernistManifesto-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-EcoModernistManifesto_8-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ecomodernism.org/manifesto/\">\"An Ecomodernist Manifesto\"</a>. <i>ecomodernism.org</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">April 17,</span> 2015</span>. <q>A good Anthropocene demands that humans use their growing social, economic, and technological powers to make life better for people, stabilize the climate, and protect the natural world.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=ecomodernism.org&amp;rft.atitle=An+Ecomodernist+Manifesto&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecomodernism.org%2Fmanifesto%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-NYT41415-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-NYT41415_9-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Eduardo Porter (April 14, 2015). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/15/business/an-environmentalist-call-to-look-past-sustainable-development.html\">\"A Call to Look Past Sustainable Development\"</a>. <i>The New York Times</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">April 17,</span> 2015</span>. <q>On Tuesday, a group of scholars involved in the environmental debate, including Professor Roy and Professor Brook, Ruth DeFries of Columbia University, and Michael Shellenberger and Ted Nordhaus of the Breakthrough Institute in Oakland, Calif., issued what they are calling the \"Eco-modernist Manifesto.\"</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=A+Call+to+Look+Past+Sustainable+Development&amp;rft.date=2015-04-14&amp;rft.au=Eduardo+Porter&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2015%2F04%2F15%2Fbusiness%2Fan-environmentalist-call-to-look-past-sustainable-development.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-EcoModernismAuthors-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-EcoModernismAuthors_10-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ecomodernism.org/authors/\">\"Authors An Ecomodernist Manifesto\"</a>. <i>ecomodernism.org</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">April 17,</span> 2015</span>. <q>As scholars, scientists, campaigners, and citizens, we write with the conviction that knowledge and technology, applied with wisdom, might allow for a good, or even great, <a href=\"/wiki/Anthropocene\" title=\"Anthropocene\">Anthropocene</a>.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=ecomodernism.org&amp;rft.atitle=Authors+An+Ecomodernist+Manifesto&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecomodernism.org%2Fauthors%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">DeFries, Ruth. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ruthdefries.com/book/big-ratchet/\">\"The Big Ratchet\"</a>. <i>Ruth DeFries</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Ruth+DeFries&amp;rft.atitle=The+Big+Ratchet&amp;rft.aulast=DeFries&amp;rft.aufirst=Ruth&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ruthdefries.com%2Fbook%2Fbig-ratchet%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-12\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">DeFries, Ruth. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ruthdefries.e3b.columbia.edu/publications/\">\"Publications\"</a>. <i>Columbia University</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Columbia+University&amp;rft.atitle=Publications&amp;rft.aulast=DeFries&amp;rft.aufirst=Ruth&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ruthdefries.e3b.columbia.edu%2Fpublications%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ARuth+DeFries\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-13\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-13\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://thebreakthrough.org/index.php/dialogue/paradigm-award-winners/ruth-defries-announced-as-2015-paradigm-award-winner\">\"Ruth DeFries Announced as 2015 Paradigm Award Winner\"</a>. The Breakthrough Institute<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">August 14,</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Ruth+DeFries+Announced+as+2015+Paradigm+Award+Winner&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fthebreakthrough.org%2Findex.php%